Class ReceivedMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.bavenir.vicinity.gatewayapi.xmpp.ReceivedMessage

  • public class ReceivedMessage
extends java.lang.Object
    This class serves as a wrapper for XMPP message, so we can add a few more attributes into it, such as request ID, time stamp etc.

      • STALE_MESSAGE_TIMEOUT

        public static final int STALE_MESSAGE_TIMEOUT
        Number of milliseconds to consider the incoming message a stale, so it can be discarded at the nearest opportunity.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • requestId

        private int requestId
        A service call to Gateway API will produce a XMPP message sent across the XMPP network for processing by a remote object. After processing a response message is received and inserted into a queue. The service that was the original sender can then sort through the queue and find a the message it is waiting for.

        private long timestamp
        UNIX time stamp generated in the moment the message arrives.
